metatags.og:description: Download scientific diagram | (a) Met Office surface analysis (‘ASXX’) showing the centre of Storm Arwen over the east coast of England at 0000 utc 27 November. The approximate track of the MSLP centre from 0000 utc 26 to 0000 utc 28 November is indicated in red. As analyses indicate the system exhibited multiple centres at certain times, the track has been simplified for clarity. The labels of the red crosses indicate the analysis time hour (utc)/date/minimum MSLP (hPa). (Original UKMO surface analysis chart Crown copyright 2021.) (b) The anomaly of the time‐integrated maximum wind speed at the 925hPa pressure level for the period 0000 utc 26 to 0000 utc 27 November, relative to the standard deviation across all grid boxes within this domain. (obtained from NWP output nudged to Global Forecast System (GFS) model analyses). from publication: Some aspects of the unusual climatology of Storm Arwen (2021) | Histogram of the difference in MSLP between 57.25°N, 7.25°W and 56.75°N, 2.25°W using hourly 0
